Ask HN: Zero-downtime migration from MongoBD to PostgresSQL
text:
Hey,

we are looking for an efficient way to migrate away from MongoDB to Postgres. Were hosted on Mongo Cloud ATM but i dont think theyll provide us a solution.

Key thing is were running a system which can not go down, and looking online i could not find anything that seems reliable and would help us to achieve that. Developing an in house solution for a one-off job also seems to be not the best one.

Maybe someone has experience regarding that, and could at least point in a good way? Would be really helpful. Thanks!

Show HN: Skeletor – lightweight React Native toolkit
text:
We built this small toolkit to speed up our onboarding & app development process in react-native with one concept behind it - "make my code short and to the point".

Its components and hooks will help resolve any pains you might have with animations, form handling & validation, screen layouts etc. It's small, purpose built, fully typed and completely dependency free.

Contributions, suggestions, requests are more than welcome on our GitHub repo.

Tell HN: How to download S3 files in 15 simple steps
text:
Background: I've used S3 to host various static content over the years, be it for emails or static websites. Today, I needed to download some of those assets. This was my journey:

1. Discover the S3 web UI won't let you download more than one file at a time 2. Install CLI: `brew install awscli` including a bunch of deps: `ca-certificates`, `openssl@1.1`, `readline`, `sqlite`, `xz`, `python@3.11`, `docutils` and `six` 3. Run `aws configure` 4. Learn what IAM is and that you not only need an access key, but also an IAM user 5. Open IAM doc link that only describes what the name requirements, object quotas, and STS(?) character limits of IAM are 6. ??? 7. Find actual article describing how to create an IAM user 8. Delete old CLI user that is 7 years old and you no longer have credentials for 8. Before creating the user, create a group 9. Attach the right permissions policies to the group. There's only 817 to chose from - easy. 10. Creating a user with the same name as the previous deleted user resurrects that user??? Yep, yep, yep, this is fine... 11. Realize I have to hard reload the page for the frontend to update my IAM user info. 2023 tech right here. 12. Create access key for the new IAM user 13. Warning pops up: "Alternatives recommended: Use the AWS CLI V2 and enable authentication through a user in IAM Identity Center." – wtf do you think I just did, buddy??? 14. Finally log into aws CLI 15. Copy files using `aws s3 cp`

breathe

Yikes!
